<subSubSection id="4A69B64E57D92348656C1DF78F518862" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" type="taxonomic notes">
<paragraph id="428104541E9F1A41E48015A9727C831D" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Taxonomic notes.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="AD80AE7D38AE3AF20378194B952302CF" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
The epithet 
<emphasis id="31742533B473686F23DF07C2E07322DA" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">autralis</emphasis>
was selected based on the restricted distribution of this species in southern Argentina. It is not possible to use 
<taxonomicName id="0CDB3C4C5793233F51A7C197F5FA409C" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Fabiana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Fabiana patagonica" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="patagonica">
<emphasis id="3F68F5082DFDE00F53E05FD226F595CC" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Fabiana patagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a specific epithet in 
<taxonomicName id="73EF85103EFE6929EDDD17A4B15A65B4" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Fabiana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Fabiana" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="8330382942A81678CC6BCD48F7FBBF7E" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Fabiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, because it is already in use in 
<taxonomicName id="96A1B3CA4D919FF23DD697ACD2BED9D7" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Fabiana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Fabiana patagonica" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="patagonica">
<emphasis id="BEE19006ABD3403298EE5493023DEB27" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Fabiana patagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Speg. 
<taxonomicName id="ADE49D53FC66AC28338AFC272FAE608C" authorityName="Alaria" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Fabiana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Fabiana australis" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="australis">
<emphasis id="EFF4A6760B07ECDF680300B178C839C2" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Fabiana australis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is one of the southernmost species of the genus. It shares with 
<taxonomicName id="72675EF746584EBCFD32FC49F17BDE84" genus="F." lsidName="F. foliosa" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="foliosa">
<emphasis id="A8F77FB7C60D5340D093EA9DC7744FA0" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">F. foliosa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="49D96C1F4CA6160E2B50C79A8439EEBF" genus="F." lsidName="F. nana" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="species" species="nana">
<emphasis id="460992DCAFCCBE940405227C6FEBB674" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">F. nana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
a similar habit forming dense cushions in dry, cold, and poor soils of Patagonian Argentina.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
