<paragraph id="C252C66403CA79A1F9C6B431C1E9B6AB" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">
Taxonomic characters differentiating 
<taxonomicName id="2ABF2FDE28D4C4E4667ADD22FAF83C19" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Calibrachoa" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Calibrachoa" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="08D9FD243123A14D8687B8AA2487B11A" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Calibrachoa</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="6ACD7A17854D22B6988BA610CE18E682" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Fabiana" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Fabiana" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A0B96E6F6437631C06C37E83228B5AB9" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Fabiana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="3DC027BF7C4378521DB6104388D39A87" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Petunia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Petunia" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="9C3F6943F3C8D4DC99BFE9E86A9E954C" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Petunia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and 
<taxonomicName id="F47F3E24E6664943B8A26FAC4B6CA124" genus="Nierembregia" lsidName="Nierembregia" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="A31C561F8C161B753FE5089FBEF8C084" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Nierembregia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are described in the following key. Geographic distribution of the four genera and 
<taxonomicName id="DAE0AA87CB1109BD8F256B31B130E3DC" authorityName="Alaria &amp; Chau &amp; Olmstead &amp; Peralta" authorityYear="2022" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Solanaceae" genus="Petunia" higherTaxonomySource="CoL" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Petunia patagonica" order="Solanales" pageId="0" pageNumber="75" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="patagonica">
<emphasis id="6400BECD22E2906D951F41A838E95805" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">Petunia patagonica</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, as well as photographs of flowers and seeds of representative species of each genus, are illustrated in Figure 
<figureCitation id="D99714E391B08ED9FD8DE7809C5F71CB" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Geographic distribution of the genera Fabiana, Calibrachoa, Petunia, and Nierembregia, and the species Fabiana australis Alaria. Flowers and seeds of representative species: Fabiana patagonica Speg (first flower scale: 2.5 mm, second flower scale: 5 mm, seed scale: 0.5 mm, surface details magnifications 600 x and 1,500 x); Calibrachoa parviflora (Juss.) D'Arcy (first flower scale: 2.5 mm, second flower scale: 5 mm, seed scale: 0.5 mm, surface details magnifications 500 x and 1,500 x); Petunia axillaris (Lam.) Britton, Sterns &amp; Poggenb. (first flower scale = 5 mm, second flower scale: 10 mm, seed scale: 0.5 mm, surface details magnifications 600 x and 1,500 x); Nierembergia pulchella Gillies ex Miers (first flower scale: 5 mm, second flower scale: 10 mm, seed scale: 0.5 mm, surface details magnifications 600 x and 1,500 x). Photograph IBODA, Flora Argentina database." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.194.68404.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/673030" pageId="0" pageNumber="75">4</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
